                Adding Text in Game Lab
Key Concepts
Text in Game Lab:

Text can be displayed on the canvas using commands like text().
You can customize the position, size, and font of the text.
Key Text Commands:

text(content, x, y): Displays the content string at position (x, y) on the canvas.
textSize(size): Sets the size of the text.
textFont(font): Sets the font of the text (optional).
fill(color): Sets the text color.
Example 1: Predicting Text Behavior
Code:

javascript
background("white");
fill("black");
textSize(30);
text("Hello, everyone", 100, 200);
Prediction:

What will show on the screen?
The text "Hello, everyone" will appear in black.
Where will it be displayed?
The text will be positioned at (100, 200) on the canvas. This means:
The text's left edge will start at x = 100.
The text's baseline (not top edge) will align with y = 200.
